Structure Title: Crystal Structure of Aquaporin Z Tetramer Reveals both Open and Closed Water-conducting Channels
Crystal Growth Procedure: 16% PEG3350, 0.75%beta-OG, 20% glycerol, 0.064 M Na Acetate, pH 4.6, VAPOR DIFFUSION, HANGING DROP, temperature 273K

Structure Title: Crystal structure of the spinach aquaporin SoPIP2;1 in an open conformation to 3.9 resolution
Electron crystallographic structure of lens Aquaporin-0 (AQP0) (lens MIP) at 1.9A resolution, in a closed pore state
Crystal Growth Procedure: 20mM MES pH 6.0, 50mM MgCl2, 5mM DTT, MICRODIALYSIS, temperature 300K

Structure Title: X-ray structure of lens Aquaporin-0 (AQP0) (lens MIP) in an open pore state
Crystal Growth Procedure: 20 mM glycine, pH 10.0   30% polyethylene glycol 1K   50 mM NaCl, VAPOR DIFFUSION, SITTING DROP, temperature 300K
